<TITLE> BCB announces Academy team for Australia tour </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Aug 16 (bdnews24.com) - The Bangladesh Cricket Board (BCB) Thursday announced a 14-meber Academy squad for the Australia tour, scheduled for August and September. The Academy team, scheduled to leave for Australia on August 23, will play one three-dayer, one four-dayer and six one-dayers against their Australian counterparts. Mehrab Hossain Jr will lead the team while Nasiruddin Faruque will be his deputy. Former Bangladesh captain Khaled Mahmud was named coach-cum-manager while Minhajul Abedin Nannu as special batting coach. Squad: Mehrab Hossain Jr (captain), Nasiruddin Faruque (vice captain), Imrul Kayes, Jahirul Islam Omi, Rakibul Hasan, Suhrawardi Shuvo, Sagir Hossain Pavel, Dollar Mahmud, Talha Jubair, Nazmul Hossain, Mahbubul Alam Robin, Mosharraf Hossain Rubel, Diman Ghosh and Nayeem Islam. Officials: Khaled Mahmud Sujan (coach-cum-manager), Minhajul Abedin Nannu (special batting coach), Wahidul Gani (spin bowling coach), Shane Ncdermott (trainer) and Bayezid (physio). bdnew
